1.title: Can We Set a Date
1.plot: For 20 years Nick Carter lived a wild life as a member of the Backstreet Boys, a hugely popular boy band. Nick thinks he's ready to finally settle down with the love of his life, his fiancée Lauren Kitt. But after spending a lifetime being available to his band and his fans, Nick has a hard time fitting the wedding into his schedule. When Nick's management team makes the Backstreet Boys new tour a top priority, Lauren wonders if Nick is able to make their marriage a priority.

2.title: A Smart Business Move
2.plot: After Nick's management team swipes aside his planned wedding date and urges him to get a pre-nup, Lauren questions Nick's ability to control his own life.

3.title: Wanna Talk About the Guest List?
3.plot: Nick and Lauren both have some family drama to contend with, and before the wedding they try to see if they can reconnect and get back on the right foot. Lauren meets her mother for a cake tasting and discovers that time doesn't heal all wounds. Meanwhile, Nick takes his brother Aaron out fishing.

4.title: You're Marrying a Fat and Stupid Man
4.plot: Though he's a successful pop star with millions of female fans, Nick has insecurities about reaching his mid-thirties being out of shape and never having finished high school. Lauren tries to console him, but since she's a fitness model and speaks multiple languages, Nick still feels a bit inadequate sometimes.

5.title: This Isn't the Nick Carter Show
5.plot: Nick is thrilled to get the chance to tour with his friend, another boy band veteran Jordan Knight, but the opportunity would conflict with his wedding date. Lauren is dismayed to hear that Nick would consider moving the date. Lauren wants a project that's not all about Nick, so she takes meetings to develop a fitness app. That night, at a charity event, Nick is reminded about the importance of what marriage means.

6.title: Tour Life
6.plot: Nick and Lauren fly to Europe for the Backstreet Boys world tour. Constant touring and living out of a bus puts a strain on the relationship. When Lauren meets up with some old friends in Paris, she's reminded of a time when she lived on her own schedule. She decides to take a breather and spend a few days in France, but Nick argues otherwise.

7.title: Dude I Love You
7.plot: It's a rocky few days before the wedding as Nick gets writer's block trying to write his vows, and his brother Aaron calls to say he can only attend the reception not the actual ceremony. Meanwhile Lauren deals with other bumps in the road to the wedding. When they hit Las Vegas for a bachelor/bachelorette weekend, Nick and Lauren find their own ways to let off some steam.

8.title: I Do
8.plot: Nick and Lauren decide to put aside the family drama and just get to the resort for the wedding weekend. A Moroccan casbah themed party breaks the ice for their guests, and Nick parties a bit too hard the night before the wedding. The day of the wedding, Lauren and the bridesmaids get emotional when Nick's Management team surprises her with a contract at the last minute. Nick has a moment with his groomsmen as well, realizing that he's finally growing up and taking responsibility.

imdb.title: I (Heart) Nick Carter
plot: This series follows the lives of engaged couple Backstreet Boys member Nick Carter and fitness competitor Lauren Kitt on their journey to the big day. Along the way dealing with management, family issues, and figuring out married life.::katyrabbits
